1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,210
Put the action principle to work.

2
00:00:02,400 --> 00:00:07,169
Next time you experience big fear or little fear, steady yourself.

3
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:13,970
Then search for an answer to this question, what kind of action can I take to conquer my fear?

4
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:18,289
Isolate your fear, then take appropriate action.

5
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:23,809
Here are some examples of fear and some possible action cures.

6
00:00:25,680 --> 00:00:27,090
Type of fear.

7
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:27,809
1.

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,010
Embarrassment because of personal appearance.

9
00:00:31,520 --> 00:00:32,289
Action.

10
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:33,250
Improve it.

11
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:35,970
Go to a barbershop or beauty salon.

12
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,169
Shine your shoes.

13
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:39,730
Get your clothes cleaned and pressed.

14
00:00:39,920 --> 00:00:42,370
In general, practice better grooming.

15
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,169
It doesn't always take new clothes.

16
00:00:45,169 --> 00:00:46,929
2.

17
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:49,890
Fear of losing an important customer.

18
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:52,850
Work doubly hard to give better service.

19
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:57,409
Correct anything that may have caused customers to lose confidence in you.

20
00:00:57,409 --> 00:00:59,010
3.

21
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:01,730
Fear of failing an examination.

22
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:05,090
Convert worry time into study time.

23
00:01:05,090 --> 00:01:06,689
4.

24
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:10,049
Fear of things totally beyond your control.

25
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:14,289
Turn your attention to helping to relieve the fear of others.

26
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:15,330
Pray.

27
00:01:15,330 --> 00:01:16,929
5.

28
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:24,689
Fear of being physically hurt by something you can't control, such as a tornado or an airplane out of control.

29
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:28,210
Switch your attention to something totally different.

30
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:31,010
Go out into your yard and pull up weeds.

31
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:32,449
Play with your children.

32
00:01:32,560 --> 00:01:33,890
Go to a movie.

33
00:01:33,890 --> 00:01:35,569
6.

34
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:39,250
Fear of what other people may think and say.

35
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:43,650
Make sure that what you plan to do is right, then do it.

36
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:48,530
No one ever does anything worthwhile for which he is not criticized.

37
00:01:48,530 --> 00:01:50,210
7.

38
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:54,130
Fear of making an investment or purchasing a home.

39
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:57,809
Analyze all factors, then be decisive.

40
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,049
Make a decision and stick with it.

41
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:01,809
Trust your own judgment.

42
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:03,569
8.

43
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:05,090
Fear of people.

44
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:07,650
Put them in proper perspective.

45
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:13,169
Remember, the other person is just another human being pretty much like yourself.

46
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:19,090
Use this two-step procedure to cure fear and win confidence.

47
00:02:19,090 --> 00:02:20,049
1.

48
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,809
Isolate your fear.

49
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:22,850
Pin it down.

50
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:25,890
Determine exactly what you are afraid of.

51
00:02:25,890 --> 00:02:27,090
2.

52
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:28,770
Then take action.

53
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:32,370
There is some kind of action for any kind of fear.

54
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:38,049
And remember, hesitation only enlarges, magnifies the fear.

55
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,730
Take action promptly.

56
00:02:39,920 --> 00:02:41,250
Be decisive.

